editorialSummary.text: Burgers, custom cakes & handmade milkshakes in a nostalgic 1950s-themed spot with a working jukebox.

originalText.text: I ordered for delivery and couldn’t be happier, I found my go to burger place in the area. The burger was perfectly tasty, great toppings and flavor. The All American Burger  was made with care and handcrafted to perfection. Sauce on it was perfect as well, one of the best burgers in Harlem. Fries were crispy and the perfect size. Great prices for what you’re getting and great quality ingredients. Everything was put together and packaged efficiently and clean. I can’t wait to come dine in. You guys are awesome!

originalText.text: When my friend and I walked in, the workers were keen to greet us in what felt like genuine friendliness. We looked around at their menu, placed our orders, were invited to take our seats, and only waited about 10 minutes for both of our orders to be made. I was pleasantly satisfied with my order of curly fries and T-Bird burger, and my friend enjoyed his food as well. I paid for everything and we left with a good taste in our mouths. The only things I had to say to not mark this with 5 stars are 1) it is a somewhat small establishment, so it can feel a little claustrophobic if more than 3 people are dining inside, 2) my shake was pretty bland, I'm sorry to say. Overall I would consider going back there, but I would suggest going when the place is empty.

originalText.text:
I'm a big foodie & I've been living in this neighborhood for over 20 years & just decided to give them a try last night. Presentation was good, the fries tray was kind of small but the burgers were decent size.
Ordered all All American Cheeseburger well done, a T Bird and small fries. The fries were a tad salty but were fried pretty well they weren't soggy.
My T-Bird was ground turkey basically w/cheddar cheese, lettuce, tomatoes & onions. It was falling apart when I got to the middle but it was seasoned well & hit different taste buds. My mother said the cheeseburger was burnt just alittle bit around the edges but it didn't kill the taste of the flavors which was good. Will recommend for those looking for a nice quick bite for your buck.

originalText.text: 10/10!!!! Made a stop here on the way to the Harlem metro north station for dinner and it was amazing! I originally saw CakeBurgers on tiktok from a series “off the eaten path” and put it on my list immediately. We got the classic burger and the all American burger and split cheese fries. We also both got a fresh squeezed limeade and a chocolate milkshake for dessert. My boyfriend thought it would be too much because I tend to over order, but it was so good we ate it all!!! It is very small inside with only 1-2 tables, but it was nice out so Evette, the owner, moved a table outside for us! She also plans to set up an awesome outdoor dining section for this summer. I will definitely be coming back here to try some cake. The owners are super nice and welcoming. Amazing small business & a great way to support the local shops in east harlem.

originalText.text: A cozy little spot with the most delicious burgers and fries. I requested and received a custom soda float, which perfectly complements the burger. My son is such a picky eater but they made the crispiest chicken bites for him and he loved it. We had the best time here.
